      <hedline>
        <hl1>Tony Blair's Modernizing Ways</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Frederica T H McRae letter on Warren Hoge's May 14 article on British Prime Min Tony Blair recalls children visiting Yorkshire Museum declaring Blair England's patron saint; photo</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Traveling in York, England, recently, I latched on to a tour group of local primary school children who were visiting the Yorkshire Museum (Warren Hoge, May 14). The museum guide stimulated group discussion by throwing out the odd question. York is the major religious center of North England, and the guide asked the children to name England's patron saint. He and I did our best to stifle our laughter at the unhesitating reply: Tony Blair.</p>
        <p>Frederica T.H. McRae  Atlanta</p>
      </block>
